    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The Barry County Health Department was established July 1, 1931 by the county board of supervisors. From the beginning the department was associated with the W.K. Kellogg Foundation, whose charter emphasized "the health, happiness and welfare of children." Originally the department had two budgets. One budget covering basic programs was funded by the county. The other, funded by the Foundation, provided for auxiliary programs that included specialized training to physicians and dentists with emphasis on maternal and child health.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The record group includes annual and monthly reports and minutes of the Michigan Community Health Program and the Hastings Health Service Committee. In addition, there are record books detailing the incidences of communicable diseases, tuberculosis, and "dangerous diseases" in the county. The photograph series includes photographs illustrating department activities. Of interest is an album, 1942, with photos of one-room schools in Barry County.</p>
    </scopecontent>
